# 33ebe0e39d9546aa93de6c3cd5d85b9a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:20
msgid "hosting.config"
msgstr ""

# e1dcc3909c8742698c4a98e9d5dec023
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:24
msgid ""
"The :file:`hosting.config` file (by default, located in "
"``/usr/local/etc/trafficserver/``) you to assign cache volumes to "
"specific origin servers and/or domains so that you can manage cache space"
" efficiently and restrict disk usage. For step-by-step instructions on "
"partitioning the cache according to origin servers and/or domains, refer "
"to :ref:`partitioning-the-cache`."
msgstr ""

# 277265a864954daf87799d0b7f614578
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:31
msgid ""
"Before you can assign cache volumes to specific origin servers and/or "
"domains, you must first partition your cache according to size and "
"protocol in the :file:`volume.config` file."
msgstr ""

# ef90f8a97ef441d5a2e49ead49ae0e8d
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:36
msgid ""
"After you modify hosting.config, navigate to the Traffic Server bin "
"directory and run :option:`traffic_ctl config reload` to apply your "
"changes."
msgstr ""

# 62f15dc2a24d4c5281f33bfd004c3d59
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:39
msgid ""
"When you apply the changes to a node in a cluster, Traffic Server "
"automatically applies the changes to all other nodes in the cluster."
msgstr ""

# 33656c79b73d4e10800608174101fc59
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:44
msgid ""
"The :file:`volume.config` configuration must be the same on all nodes in "
"a cluster."
msgstr ""

# 2cddb8c392784ea084f856631c6fea44
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:47
msgid "Format"
msgstr ""

# a8a942cbe6414dd7b9aa6e6b786f9a07
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:49
msgid ""
"Each line in the :file:`hosting.config` file must have one of the "
"following formats::"
msgstr ""

# f2567c05e9bb4143ac8183601c802bfd
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:55
msgid ""
"where ``HOST`` is the fully-qualified hostname of the origin server whose"
" content you want to store on a particular volume (for example, "
"``www.myhost.com``); ``DOMAIN`` is the domain whose content you want to "
"store on a particular partition(for example, ``mydomain.com``); and "
"``NUMBERS`` is a comma-separated list of the partitions on which you want"
" to store the content that belongs to the origin server or domain listed."
" The partition numbers must be valid numbers listed in the "
"file:`volume.config`."
msgstr ""

# 3127fc7d61a84470800ea92ec51c0779
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:64
msgid ""
"**Note:** To allocate more than one partition to an origin server or "
"domain, you must enter the partitions in a comma-separated list on one "
"line, as shown in the example below. The :file:`hosting.config`  file "
"cannot contain multiple entries for the same origin server or domain."
msgstr ""

# d4903b1b146343939e40ba5fe45243e7
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:71
msgid "Generic Partition"
msgstr ""

# ce2868f1a37e4df08b6a726082c4ee15
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:73
msgid ""
"When configuring the :file:`hosting.config` file, you must assign a "
"generic volume to use for content that does not belong to any of the "
"origin servers or domains listed. If all volumes for a particular origin "
"server become corrupt, Traffic Server will also use the generic volume to"
" store content for that origin server."
msgstr ""

# 0d6a8ac16e7b4a25bcbfc19cda60a3ac
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:79
msgid "The generic volume must have the following format::"
msgstr ""

# 90c0526c06294699a4645a57c7b2fac3
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:83
msgid "where ``NUMBERS`` is a comma-separated list of generic volumes."
msgstr ""

# 1f5e9df145b443eda1f4d8f25fddcb11
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:87
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

# 5a2d8003b1714dc6aa0f25d5a5137cb8
#: ../../admin-guide/files/hosting.config.en.rst:89
msgid ""
"The following example configures Traffic Server to store content from the"
" domain ``mydomain.com`` in volume 1 and content from ``www.myhost.com`` "
"in volume 2. Traffic Server stores content from all other origin servers "
"in volumes 3 and 4."
msgstr ""

